      {
        "id": "mineru_jiaocaineedrop_chap02.pdf_16_12",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Summarizing In what ways was",
        "bbox": [
          0.6752941176470588,
          0.5799233716475096,
          0.8705882352941177,
          0.5952490421455938
        ],
        "order": 13
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_jiaocaineedrop_chap02.pdf_16_13",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "England permissive wit its American colonies?",
        "bbox": [
          0.527843137254902,
          0.597088122605364,
          0.796078431372549,
          0.6124137931034482
        ],
        "order": 14
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_jiaocaineedrop_chap02.pdf_16_24",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "7. Analyzing Charts Study the chart on page 54 on Spanish, English, and French colonization. In political organi- zation, what was a trait of the English colonies that the French and Spanish colonies did not share?",
        "bbox": [
          0.6282352941176471,
          0.720919540229885,
          0.8862745098039215,
          0.8128735632183908
        ],
        "order": 20
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_jiaocaineedrop_chap02.pdf_16_19",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "1. Define: pacifism, debtor. 2.Identify: English Civil War, William Penn, James Oglethorpe. 3. Summarize how the Quakers came to have a colony of their own.",
        "bbox": [
          0.0596078431372549,
          0.7215325670498084,
          0.31529411764705884,
          0.7981609195402298
        ],
        "order": 21
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_jiaocaineedrop_chap02.pdf_16_22",
        "observed_type": "list",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "5. Analyzing Why did England regard the Dutch and Spanish presence in North America as a threat, and how did England respond? 6. Categorizing Use agraphic organizer similar to the one below to list the reasons that the listed colonies were founded.",
        "bbox": [
          0.34352941176470586,
          0.7215325670498084,
          0.6062745098039216,
          0.8435249042145594
        ],
        "order": 22
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_jiaocaineedrop_chap02.pdf_16_20",
        "observed_type": "title",
        "canon_role": "section_header",
        "text": "Reviewing Themes",
        "bbox": [
          0.12627450980392158,
          0.8079693486590038,
          0.2564705882352941,
          0.8232950191570881
        ],
        "order": 23
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_jiaocaineedrop_chap02.pdf_16_21",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "4.Global Connections After Charles Il became king, why did the English gov- ernment openly work to promote colo- nization in North America?",
        "bbox": [
          0.0603921568627451,
          0.826360153256705,
          0.3184313725490196,
          0.8870498084291187
        ],
        "order": 25
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_jiaocaineedrop_chap02.pdf_16_26",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "8. Persuasive Writing Imagine you have been hired by the proprietors of New Jersey to persuade settlers to come to their colony. Write an editorial for a newspaper in England to convince people to settle in New Jersey.",
        "bbox": [
          0.6298039215686274,
          0.842911877394636,
          0.8901960784313725,
          0.9354789272030651
        ],
